								<div class="title" id="post-title-2544289">
																		art imitates life
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/a-random-day" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1841781); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1841781&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610227397" alt="A Random Day" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1841781)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/a-random-day" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1841781); return false;" >A Random Day</a></span> <span class="odate time_1469583831 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">27 Jul 2016 01:43</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2544289">
									

<p>From conception to post: 22 hours 25 minutes.</p>
<p>Theme song is <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=UMJm_97QXHA">&quot;Francis Forever&quot;</a> by <a href="https://mitski.bandcamp.com">Mitski</a>.</p>
<p>Huge thanks to Athena_Grey and Some_Potato for their extensive crit and helping me make the ending not confusing garbage.<br />
Many thanks to GreenWolf, minmin, TyGently, and Tuomey Tombstone for their feedback.<br />
Many thanks to Ap0plexic, Levi, AidenEldritch, and everyone else in chat who read this and liked it.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/project-proposal-2004-024">Guy Chesapeake</a> was created by Zolgamax.<br />
The <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/project-proposal-1964-238">transistorized positronic cognition matrix</a> was created by Asimov and referenced by Smapti.<br />
<a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/goc-hub-page">Servants of the Silicon Nornir</a> were presumably created by DrClef.<br />
The ending was heavily influenced by Kalinin's essay on <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/metacritique-two">anomalous art</a>.<br />
While Arvind Desai's only other appearance of note is in the Resurrection canon, this tale is not intended for that canon. I link them merely to expand upon the relationship of father and son.</p>
<p>See more of my work on my <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/dr-arvind-desais-personnel-file">author page</a>!</p>

							</div>

								
